This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sentiment analysis and emotion recognition tasks, which are common topics in natural language processing. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel model for learning correlations between text, audio, and video features, which is a relevant topic in multimodal language analysis. 

The paper also touches upon topics related to computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) as it considers the visual and acoustic properties of the input data. 

Furthermore, the paper uses deep canonical correlation analysis (DCCA) to learn the embeddings, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). 

Finally, the paper also discusses ablation studies, which are a common evaluation technique in software engineering (cs.SD).
